page.title: 09KINGLEY VALE_FLORA & FAUNA
page.content: Of the many{flowers}in Kingley Vale the most interesting are the{orchids.} These include the spotted, fragrant, bee, pyramid and fly orchids. The{birds}most often seen breeding are chaffinch,robin,pigeon,blackbird, wren,dunnock,pheasant,coal tit,willow warbler,great tit,whitethroat,yellow hammer,goldcrest,bullfinch,chiffchaff, song thrush,blue tit and blackcap. The{animals}include fallow deer,roe deer,hare,rabbit,fox,badger,stoat, weasel,feral cat,hedgehog,common brown rat,shrew,grey squirrel,vole, adder,lizard and mice. There are many{butterflies,}the most common being meadow brown,hedge brown and brimstone. {Trees.}Ash,oak,hawthorn,yew,privet, buckthorn,dogwood,spindle and blackthorn.Kingley Vale has the finest {yew forest}in Europe.
